# Main Directory Structure Guide

This guide outlines key directories in the "Family Stalking" Android project.

- **`app/`**: Main application module.
    - **`app/src/main/java/com/familystalking/app/`**: Kotlin source code.
        - `data/`: Data layer (repositories, data sources).
        - `di/`: Dependency injection.
        - `domain/`: Domain layer (use cases, models).
        - `presentation/`: UI layer (ViewModels, UI components).
        - `ui/theme/`: App themes and UI styling.
    - **`app/src/main/res/`**: Android resources.
        - `drawable/`: Image and icon resources.
        - `mipmap-*/`: Launcher icons.
        - `values/`: Strings, colors, styles.
- **`.github/workflows/`**: GitHub Actions CI/CD workflows.
- **`config/detekt/`**: Detekt static analysis configuration (e.g., `detekt.yml`).
- **`gradle/wrapper/`**: Gradle wrapper files.
- **[build.gradle.kts](mdc:build.gradle.kts)**: Root Gradle build script.
- **`app/build.gradle.kts`**: App module Gradle build script (typically).
- **[settings.gradle.kts](mdc:settings.gradle.kts)**: Gradle settings, defines modules.
- **[README.md](mdc:README.md)**: Main project documentation.

For detailed Kotlin package structure, explore `app/src/main/java/com/familystalking/app/`.
